== Synopsis == <a name="Synopsis"></a>

This is a plugin for [http://code.google.com/p/ps3mediaserver/ PS3 Media Server] (PMS) that adds configurable support for web video streaming.

== Prerequisites == <a name="Prerequisites"></a>

Due to an [http://code.google.com/p/ps3mediaserver/issues/detail?id=766 issue] in the Mac OS X build of PMS, PMSEncoder doesn't currently work on Macs. In addition, PMS doesn't support web streams for the Xbox 360. PMSEncoder should work on all other platforms/renderers supported by PS3 Media Server.

These instructions assume you have the [http://ps3mediaserver.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=2&t=3217 latest version] of PS3 Media Server, the [http://www.java.com/en/download/index.jsp latest version] of Java, and a recent MEncoder.

== Installation == <a name="Install"></a>

* download the [http://github.com/downloads/chocolateboy/pmsencoder/pmsencoder-1.3.0.jar PMSEncoder jar file] and place it in the PMS `plugins` directory
* shut down PMS; open `PMS.conf` in a text editor; and add `pmsencoder` to the front of the list of engines e.g.
  * `engines = pmsencoder,mencoder,tsmuxer,mplayeraudio` &c.
* restart PMS

## Upgrading <a name="Upgrade"></a>

To upgrade to a new version of the plugin, simply replace the old jar file in the `plugins` directory with the [http://github.com/downloads/chocolateboy/pmsencoder/pmsencoder-1.3.0.jar new version] and restart PMS.

## Uninstalling <a name="Uninstall"></a>

To uninstall PMSEncoder, remove the jar file from the `plugins` directory and remove `pmsencoder,` from the list of engines in
`PMS.conf`.

