== Tips == <a name="Tips"></a>

* To work around the PMS [http://code.google.com/p/ps3mediaserver/issues/detail?id=759 bug] that causes web video playback to be delayed for ~40s, uncheck "HTTP Engine V2" in the PMS "General Configuration" tab. This can also be done by setting `http_engine_v2 = false` in PMS.conf. Then restart PMS. See [[#HTTPEngine|below]] for caveats.
* To take PMSEncoder for a spin, try [http://github.com/chocolateboy/pmsencoder/raw/master/misc/conf/WEB.conf this WEB.conf], which contains a list of feeds that are regularly tested and updated.
* The [https://code.google.com/p/ps3mediaservercontrib/ Community Beta] of PMS includes a [https://code.google.com/p/ps3mediaserver/issues/detail?id=757 patch] that
  restores support for [http://www.gametrailers.com/rssgenform.php GameTrailers feeds].

== Troubleshooting == <a name="Troubleshooting"></a>

* Internet Explorer saves .jar files as .zip files. Either save the file with a [http://www.mozilla.com/firefox/ different] [http://www.google.com/chrome browser], or rename it, replacing the .zip extension with .jar.
* <a name="HTTPEngine"></a>If you [[#Tips|disabled "HTTP Engine V2"]], try re-enabling it as some renderers, such as the Sony Bravia KDL-37V5500, require it.
* If PMS.conf doesn't exist (see [http://ps3mediaserver.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=6&t=3507&p=32731#p32731 here] for the default locations), create it by clicking the "Save" icon in the PMS GUI.
* If the list of engines doesn't exist in PMS.conf, follow the instructions [http://ps3mediaserver.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=6&t=7435&p=34674#p34674 here].
* Make sure there's only one version of the plugin in the `plugins` directory.
* Make sure the edited PMS.conf is the one PMS is using (search the filesystem for other copies).
* Make sure `pmsencoder` is still first in the engines list.
* Make sure `mencoder_path` is not set (or is not pointing to the old, standalone version of PMSEncoder).
* Make sure the error is reproducible after a PMS restart. Caching in PMS and/or the PS3 often produces one-off errors.
* Check the PMS trace, PMS debug.log, and pmsencoder.log (which should be in the same directory as the debug.log) for
  errors.

## Reporting Issues <a name="Help"></a>

Please do the following when reporting any issues:

1. restart (or start) PMS
2. try to stream a web video
3. wait until it fails
4. post your PMS.conf, pmsencoder.log and debug.log (as a zipped attachment)

